ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.140              Enzyme
NAME        2-hydroxy-1,4-benzoxazin-3-one monooxygenase;
            BX5 (gene name);
            CYP71C3 (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     2-hydroxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one,NAD(P)H:oxygen oxidoreductase (N-hydroxylating)
REACTION    2-hydroxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one + NAD(P)H + H+ + O2 = 2,4-dihydroxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one + NAD(P)+ + H2O [RN:R07423]
ALL_REAC    R07423
SUBSTRATE   2-hydroxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one;
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     2,4-dihydroxy-2H-1,4-benzoxazin-3(4H)-one [CPD:C15770];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in the biosynthesis of protective and allelophatic benzoxazinoids in some plants, most commonly from the family of Poaceae (grasses). It is a member of the cytochrome P450 dependent monooxygenases.
